NextSource Materials has announced that its construction team is now setup at the Molo Graphite Mine site in Madagascar and civil and earthworks have been initiated in preparation for the delivery and installation of the processing plant. The offsite fabrication and construction of the auxiliary buildings and structures has also been completed and these are in the process of being delivered to the mine site. President and CEO, Craig Scherba commented: “With the mobilization of construction crews to the mine site and initiation of civils and earthworks, we have reached yet another key milestone towards commissioning of the Molo Graphite mine later this year.” Seeking Alpha says NextSource Materials one of 3 Stocks For The Impending Commodity Supercyclehttps://t.co/xtJtMxHYzI